Articles.Content:
I have 2 major problems with playing with DMP and carrer mode.

I have a server on my computer, and we are 2 players.

First problem is the severe loss of reputation whenever another player recovers his ship, (or crashes his ship). DMP thinks the ship is lost, and the kerbal is killed or MIA. So it applies a reputation penalty. Would it be possible to set a flag to the Kerbals and Ships so that the last user "owns" this kerbal or ship. And in case any of them are lost it's only applied to the "owner"?

The other problem is the Desynch of missing kerbals, and duplication of them. When we recover and only 1 player is loggged in to the game, everything is fine. But when 2 players are logged in and we recover all sorts of crazy stuff happends to those kerbals. It seems they have a hard time getting expirience. And they are sometimes renamed, and sometimes KIA/MIA.

I really wish i could contribute to solve this problem by changing the code. But i'm not skilled enough and have no knowledge of the code of this mod.

As it is now, carrer mode is unplayable with DMP. And it's rather sad.

If possible, It would be nice to have a COOP-carrer mode. Where you can share science tree, credits, reputation, and kerbals. If that makes it any easyer to code in. Have the DMP mod use only 1 set of files to read of and send to each client. Than we could also share the KSC buildings and upgrades, and even active missions.. But i'm not sure if this is possible.

Right, so I'm setting up a server for some friends and we all want to run a science mode with custom difficulty.  However, even though there is the option to select custom difficulty in the server config, there is no list of options to actually specify the custom settings.  Hopefully one of you fine folks has an answer for me, please?
the dmp client window doesent open on my ksp. why?
I'm playing with 2 other friends and we were wondering if it was possible to play on the same ship. If so, how?

On 30. 4. 2017 at 3:06 PM, megaspeeder said:

I'm playing with 2 other friends and we were wondering if it was possible to play on the same ship. If so, how?

You cannot play on the same ship with all. Only one can control the ship at the time and the other have to spectate the ship without any control authority. Unfortunately...

Hope that helps.  and save you time figuring out how to do it.

Right, so I'm setting up a server for some friends and we all want to run a career mode with custom difficulty.  However, even though there is the option to select custom difficulty in the server config, there is no list of options to actually specify the custom settings.  Is there a way to fix this? I'm sure a lot of other people want this too.
No idea, sorry. Ask devs of the mod.  @godarklight?

Right, so I played Science mode on DMP with a friend and I discovered a pretty game-breaking exploit. I was able to basically give myself unlimited science and unlock all nodes pretty much instantly after joining.

Repro steps: (To the moderator reading/hopefully approving this, I wanted to send the developer(s) a private message about this instead of posting it publicly. Could you maybe do that for me and remove it from the post? I don't have the minimum 5 posts to do it myself yet and I'd rather not make useless posts to fill the quota.)

  1. Join any server on Science/Career mode
  2. Make a quicksave of the game
  3. Navigate to Kerbal Space Program/saves/DarkMultiPlayer
  4. Open the quicksave file (quicksave.sfs in my case) in a plain text editor (I used Notepad++)
  5. Look for where it says: name = ResearchAndDevelopment - there should be a line under that saying: sci = <Number> - change that number to however many Science points you want
  6. Save the quicksave file
  7. Load the quicksave in Kerbal Space Program 
  8. Head into the R&D building and unlock the research nodes you want
  9. Re-join the server

And the server just takes it as valid. The nodes stay unlocked and I can play as though I had unlocked them legitimately.

Ya that's editing the game save file. Of course DMP is going to allow it, it has no way of knowing that you edited it. It also doesn't apply to just science, you could put an entire ship into orbit without even opening KSP by editing the save file if you knew the right things to add in.

I actually tested this. Loading a quicksave with a craft in orbit in a DMP server doesn't put the craft on the server - other players can't see it, and rejoining (and thus re-syncing the crafts with the server) causes it to disappear. The server syncs science (and all other stats) in the same way, but doesn't verify if an action taken by the player could actually have been legitimate.

The server knows when I take measurements, when I recover vessels and how much science I get from that. It should keep count as well, and in that way it would be easily possible to detect if the player has tampered with their stats. Every properly made multiplayer game verifies client messages on the server to make sure clients aren't cheating.

One of the strengths of KSP is the freedom to do pretty much whatever you want in the game. Limiting things wouldn't be good for everyone. Of course it could be configurable if the server check or not, but there are way worse things to fix right now.

Woah, I hadn't been keeping track here.

There's a lot of HAYO things about DMP, and I'm not sure if I ever should have even tried to support career mode as it's not something I play, and I'd much rather spend my time working on the general jankiness of DMP itself that effects everyone. I can't think of how to prevent the sfs cheat without disabling reverting / quickloading / quicksaving entirely...

@JamesL86 in case you're still wondering, it's in the Settings folder. The file is only created when you set the server to custom.

@ChainZ186 it works on 64bit, but I've addressed this in dev (supporting 1.2.2 still) and unstable (1.2.9). We initialised DMP differently to what's normal without realising it until now

@megaspeeder two people in the same ship will put one of them into spectate mode, as for dual control, it's not something I've thought out all that much, and the only thing I can think of is allowing a pilot to give control to a spectator

@VolcanoINC career mode was a mistake.

@Varsi

DMP is a single player game where roughly the same thing happens

@damian0816 DMP 0.2.4.2 supports 1.2.2, so does "dev" currently, "unstable" currently supports 1.2.9.

My development branch will always support the latest version of KSP, it's essentially "release with hotfixes" when I actually work on it. Unstable is for things I think aren't ready, or for prereleases.

Please continue with career support. 

-Devan
